206\\\",\\\"static/chunks/7206-1c8c946f4e44e54c.js\\\",\\\"6107\\\",\\\"static/chunks/6107-1b6596bba5b5f106.js\\\",\\\"4561\\\",\\\"static/chunks/4561-f94d69f802929185.js\\\",\\\"804\\\",\\\"static/chunks/app/cities/%5Bslug%5D/page-8f8b55ea1a381eb4.js\\\"],\\\"default\\\"]\\n2d:T1dd8,\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"FAQPage\\\",\\\"mainEntity\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"How many dog parks are available in Gardena?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Gardena has 3 dog parks and dog-friendly establishments, including traditional outdoor dog parks, indoor dog parks, and dog-friendly businesses like restaurants and shops. Each type offers unique benefits for different situations and dog personalities.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Are there any indoor dog parks in the USA?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Yes! The United States is home to hundreds of indoor dog parks, and the industry is growing rapidly. IndoorDogPark.org maintains the most comprehensive directory available, currently tracking over 360 verified facilities across 155 cities nationwide. These climate-controlled spaces solve real problems for dog owners. In cities like Phoenix where summer temperatures can exceed 110°F, or Chicago where winter brings sub-zero temperatures for months, indoor parks become essential. They're also invaluable in rainy regions like Seattle or Portland, where outdoor parks stay muddy for much of the year. Our directory includes detailed profiles for each facility: amenities, pricing structures, operating hours, vaccination requirements, and real visitor experiences. We've aggregated over 106,000 user reviews from Google, Yelp, and other platforms to help you make informed decisions. Popular metro areas with the most options include Los Angeles (23 indoor facilities), Chicago (18 facilities), and New York City (15 facilities). But we've also documented smaller markets like Bend, Oregon, and Asheville, North Carolina, where innovative entrepreneurs are meeting local demand. To explore options near you, visit our main directory page or browse by state. Each listing includes photos, direct contact information, and links to facility websites where you can check current availability and make reservations.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Are dog parks in Gardena free to use?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Most traditional outdoor dog parks in public spaces are free to use. However, indoor dog parks and specialized facilities typically require membership fees or day passes. Dog-friendly establishments like restaurants may have minimum purchase requirements or special pet menus.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"What are the requirements to visit dog parks in Gardena?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Most dog parks require that your dog be current on vaccinations (rabies, DHPP), licensed, and well-behaved. Some indoor facilities may require proof of vaccinations, health certificates, or temperament assessments. Always check specific park rules before visiting.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"What's the best time to visit dog parks in Gardena?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Early mornings (6–9 AM) and early evenings (4–7 PM) are typically the busiest times, offering great socialization opportunities. Midday visits are usually quieter, better for dogs who may be overwhelmed by crowds. Weekends are generally busier than weekdays. Consider your dog's personality and social comfort level when planning visits.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Where to go with a dog when it's raining?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Rainy days don't have to mean canceled playtime. Indoor dog parks are specifically designed for exactly this scenario, offering climate-controlled environments where dogs can exercise and socialize safely. Our directory lists over 360 indoor facilities across the country. Many feature specialized surfaces like K9Grass or rubberized flooring that stay clean and dry regardless of weather. These surfaces are easier on joints than concrete and reduce injury risk compared to muddy outdoor parks. Beyond dedicated indoor parks, consider these alternatives: • Pet stores with play areas: Chains like PetSmart and Petco sometimes host indoor play sessions. • Dog-friendly cafes and restaurants: Many now welcome well-behaved dogs indoors, perfect for socialization in a calmer setting. • Indoor training facilities: Often open their spaces for play sessions between classes. • Doggy daycare centers: Many offer drop-in playtime options for non-members. Pro tip: Indoor facilities get significantly busier during bad weather, so call ahead or book reservations when possible. Many also offer online booking systems for convenience. Bonus: Most indoor parks include dog wash stations, so your pup can get clean before the ride home—no muddy paws in your car. Explore our directory to find indoor options near you, and filter by amenities like \\\\\\\"dog wash\\\\\\\" or \\\\\\\"separate small dog areas\\\\\\\" to find exactly what you need.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Are there any size restrictions or separate areas for different sized dogs?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Many dog parks in Gardena offer separate areas for small dogs (under 25 lbs) and large dogs (over 25 lbs). This helps ensure safe play experiences. However, not all parks have this separation, so it's important to check ahead and supervise your dog's interactions.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"What should I bring when visiting a dog park in Gardena?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Essential items include: a leash (for entering and exiting), poop bags, fresh water and a bowl, your dog's vaccination records (especially for indoor facilities), and your phone for emergencies. Optional items include toys (check park rules first), treats for training, and a first-aid kit.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Are there indoor dog park options available in Gardena?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Yes. Our directory currently lists 1 indoor dog park in Gardena. Use the “Indoor Dog Park” filter on this page to jump straight to climate-controlled options.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"What is the most dog friendly city in the USA?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"This question sparks lively debates among dog owners, and the answer depends on what you value most. Based on our analysis of over 360 facilities across 155 cities, here's what the data reveals: California dominates in sheer numbers: Los Angeles, San Diego, and San Francisco collectively host 50+ indoor dog parks. But quantity isn't everything. Cities consistently ranking high for overall dog-friendliness include: • San Francisco: Over 40% of households include dogs (above the 38% national average), extensive off-leash beaches, and one of the highest concentrations of dog parks per capita. • Portland, Oregon: Known for progressive pet policies, abundant green spaces, and a culture where dogs are welcome almost everywhere—including many restaurants and breweries. • Seattle: Over 14 off-leash areas plus multiple indoor facilities, making it ideal for a city that gets 150+ rainy days annually. • Austin, Texas: Boasts some of the largest dog parks in the country, plus a vibrant dog-friendly dining scene. • Denver: High altitude doesn't stop Coloradans—the city maintains excellent park facilities and welcoming policies. However, \\\\\\\"friendliness\\\\\\\" extends beyond park counts. Factors like pet-friendly rental policies, veterinary care access, breed restrictions, and community culture matter just as much. Our directory lets you explore by city to see specific offerings. Check out our city guides for detailed breakdowns of parks, amenities, and local pet policies. We also maintain guides for major metro areas on our blog, covering everything from best parks to dog-friendly neighborhoods.\\\"}}]}\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"26:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"script\\\",null,{\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/ld+json\\\",\\\"suppressHydrationWarning\\\":true,\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"$2d\\\"}}]\\n27:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"script\\\",null,{\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/ld+json\\\",\\\"suppressHydrationWarning\\\":true,\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"{\\\\\\\"@context\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://schema.org\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"itemListElement\\\\\\\":[{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"ListItem\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":1,\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Home\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"ListItem\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":2,\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"California Dog Parks\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"ListItem\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":3,\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Gardena\\\\\\\"}]}\\\"}}]\\n28:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L11\\\",null,{\\\"variant\\\":\\\"light\\\"}]\\n29:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L2e\\\",null,{\\\"items\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"city-hero\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"City Overview\\\",\\\"level\\\":1},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"city-insights\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Quick Facts\\\",\\\"level\\\":1},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"city-comparison\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Top Comparisons\\\",\\\"level\\\":1},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"park-collections\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Park Collections\\\",\\\"level\\\":1},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"neighborhood-clusters\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Neighborhoods\\\",\\\"level\\\":1},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"park-types-guide\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Park Type Guide\\\",\\\"level\\\":1},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"map-and-neighborhoods\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Map \\u0026 Neighborhoods\\\",\\\"level\\\":1},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"planning-essentials\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Planning Essentials\\\",\\\"level\\\":1},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"expert-tips\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Expert Advice\\\",\\\"level\\\":1},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"park-directory\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Full Directory\\\",\\\"level\\\":1},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"owner-cta\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Owner \\u0026 Franchise\\\",\\\"level\\\":1},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"faq-section\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"FAQs\\\",\\\"level\\\":1},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"related-resources\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"More Resources\\\",\\\"level\\\":1}]}]\\n33:T615,\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"Perched in Gardena, South Bay Dog Training Center delivers a dog park experience where energetic romps and mindful training feel perfectly balanced. Located in Gardena, CA, the park is tucked near 546 W 182nd St, Gardena, CA 90248 and easy to reach for commuters and weekend adventurers alike. Guests rave about its 5.0-star average across 3 reviews, pointing to spotless grounds, intuitive traffic flow, and staff who remember every pup's quirks. The campus layers mature trees with long sight lines so guardians can relax while still keeping eyes on the action. Morning, afternoon, and twilight blocks are thoughtfully staggered to keep crowds light and vibes relaxed. Access runs on membership memberships, with flexible passes that welcome both spontaneous drop-ins and devoted regulars.\\n\\nExpansive turf runs, agility challenges, and shaded rest nooks stretch across the property so dogs can sprint, sniff, and reset without ever feeling crowded. South Bay Dog Training Center curates small-group play dates, confidence-building agility rotations, and gentle introductions for new rescues. Weekly enrichment labs, pop-up adoption drives, and local vendor markets keep Gardena's canine calendar fresh. Certified behavior teams circulate through each yard, coaching leash manners and offering quick progress reports. Health-forward protocols guide every visit at South Bay Dog Training Center, from double-gated entries to staff-monitored hydration breaks. Check http://www.southbaydogs.com/ for day passes, vaccination policies, and community spotlights.\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"34:T64a,\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"South Park Doggie - Adventureland (South Bay) anchors Gardena's dog-loving rhythm as a dog park that marries expansive play yards with concierge-level care. Located in Gardena, CA, the park is tucked near 945 W 190th St, Gardena, CA 90248 and easy to reach for commuters and weekend adventurers alike. Guests rave about its 4.8-star average across 232 reviews, pointing to spotless grounds, intuitive traffic flow, and staff who remember every pup's quirks. The campus layers mature trees with long sight lines so guardians can relax while still keeping eyes on the action. Morning, afternoon, and twilight blocks are thoughtfully staggered to keep crowds light and vibes relaxed. Access runs on membership memberships, with flexible passes that welcome both spontaneous drop-ins and devoted regulars.\\n\\nExpansive turf runs, agility challenges, and shaded rest nooks stretch across the property so dogs can sprint, sniff, and reset without ever feeling crowded. South Park Doggie - Adventureland (South Bay) curates small-group play dates, confidence-building agility rotations, and gentle introductions for new rescues. Weekly enrichment labs, pop-up adoption drives, and local vendor markets keep Gardena's canine calendar fresh. Certified behavior teams circulate through each yard, coaching leash manners and offering quick progress reports. Health-forward protocols guide every visit at South Park Doggie - Adventureland (South Bay), from double-gated entries to staff-monitored hydration breaks. Check https://www.southparkadventureland.com/ for day passes, vaccination policies, and community spotlights.\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"35:T5a7,\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"South Park Doggie Pawcademy is a premier dog school and theme park that offers an innovative, fun-filled environment where dogs can thrive. Located in a spacious, beautifully designed park, we provide a variety of services focused on socialization, physical fitness, and mental development. Our carefully crafted curriculum, led by experienced trainers, ensures that each dog receives personalized attention and a learning experience tailored to their needs. Whether your dog is working on obedience, agility, or socializing with new friends, our interactive classes and themed adventure zones make learning exciting. Plus, with seasonal Paw Social events, our park serves as a community hub where pet parents can connect, share tips, and enjoy the company of other dog lovers.\\n\\nWhat makes South Park Doggie Pawcademy truly unique is the combination of education and entertainment. Our state-of-the-art facilities feature dog-friendly play zones, challenging obstacle courses, and relaxation areas, ensuring dogs have plenty of space to explore, play, and unwind. We also offer premium staycare memberships for those looking for year-round accommodations, with discounts and perks for frequent visitors. Our goal is to provide a safe, enriching environment that supports both dogs' development and the bond between pet parents and their furry companions. Join us today and discover why we’re the ultimate destination for dogs and their families!\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"2a:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"main\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"city-page-layout\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mobile-toc-button\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L2f\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mobile-toc-trigger\\\",\\\"targetSelector\\\":\\\".table-of-contents\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"i\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"bi bi-list-ul\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":\\\"Contents\\\"}]]}]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",null,{\\\"id\\\":\\\"city-hero\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"city-hero-section \\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"section-shell city-hero-shell\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"city-hero-copy\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"hero-breadcrumbs\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L12\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Home\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"i\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"bi bi-chevron-right\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":\\\"California Dog Parks\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"i\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"bi bi-chevron-right\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"strong\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":\\\"Gardena\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"hero-eyebrow\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"City spotlight\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h1\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":\\\"Indoor Dog Park in Gardena, CA\\\"}],\\\"$undefined\\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"hero-description\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Scale your urban pet lifestyle in Gardena, where community green spaces and climate-controlled enrichment meet.\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"city-rich-description\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"0\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"rich-description-paragraph\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Gardena, California, is a diverse residential hub in the South Bay where the \\\\\\\"apartment dog\\\\\\\" lifestyle is a common reality. Local favorites like Arthur Lee Johnson Memorial Park and Thornburg Park offer essential green spaces for daily walks and community connection. However, the Los Angeles Basin frequently experiences heatwaves and seasonal smog, which can compromise air quality for active pets. Learning \\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L12\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/how-it-works\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"_blank\\\",\\\"rel\\\":\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"rich-link\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"how indoor play works\\\"}],null,\\\" is increasingly important for Gardena owners seeking a safe, filtered environment.\\\"]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"rich-description-paragraph\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Per Gardena Municipal Code, dogs must be secured on a maximum six-foot leash in public spaces, emphasizing safety in this busy urban landscape. While the nearby Redondo Beach Dog Park provides a coastal escape, the daily need for reliable exercise leads residents to seek out local \\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L12\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/training-facilities\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"_blank\\\",\\\"rel\\\":\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"rich-link\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"training facilities\\\"}],null,\\\". By balancing city life with structured play, Gardena pet parents ensure their dogs remain socialized and healthy. This proactive approach to pet care makes Gardena a committed community for responsible Southern California dog owners.\\\"]}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"hero-cta-row\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L2f\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"hero-cta primary\\\",\\\"targetId\\\":\\\"park-directory\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"i\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"bi bi-list-check\\\"}],\\\"Browse directory\\\"]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L2f\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"hero-cta ghost\\\",\\\"targetId\\\":\\\"map-and-neighborhoods\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"i\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"bi bi-geo-alt\\\"}],\\\"Open map\\\"]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L12\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/list-your-park\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"hero-cta text-link\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"i\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"bi bi-plus-circle\\\"}],\\\"Submit a park\\\"]}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"hero-footnotes\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",\\\"Data refreshed weekly\\\",{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"i\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"bi bi-sparkles\\\"}],\\\" \\\",\\\"Data refreshed weekly\\\"]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",\\\"Live availability coming soon\\\",{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"i\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"bi bi-sparkles\\\"}],\\\" \\\",\\\"Live availability coming soon\\\"]}]]}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"city-hero-visual\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"hero-image-card\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L30\\\",null,{\\\"src\\\":\\\"/images/cities/gardena-ca/hero.webp\\\",\\\"alt\\\":\\\"Gardena dog park landscape\\\",\\\"fill\\\":true,\\\"priority\\\":true,\\\"sizes\\\":\\\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 540px\\\",\\\"unoptimized\\\":true}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"hero-image-gradient\\\"}]]}]}]]}]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L31\\\",null,{\\\"city\\\":\\\"Gardena\\\",\\\"state\\\":\\\"CA\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",null,{\\\"id\\\":\\\"city-insights\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"city-insights-section\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"section-shell\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L32\\\",null,{\\\"parks\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"ChIJ4UTYHgrLwoARK8cAbLx6xVs\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"South Bay Dog Training Center\\\",\\\"businessType\\\":\\\"Dog Park\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"$33\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"south-bay-dog-training-center\\\",\\\"address\\\":\\\"546 W 182nd St\\\",\\\"street\\\":\\\"546 W 182nd St\\\",\\\"city\\\":\\\"Gardena\\\",\\\"state\\\":\\\"CA\\\",\\\"zipCode\\\":\\\"90248\\\",\\\"full_address\\\":\\\"546 W 182nd St, Gardena, CA 90248\\\",\\\"latitude\\\":33.8697248,\\\"longitude\\\":-118.2831183,\\\"googlePlaceId\\\":\\\"ChIJ4UTYHgrLwoARK8cAbLx6xVs\\\",\\\"phone\\\":\\\"(562) 244-8126\\\",\\\"website\\\":\\\"http://www.southbaydogs.com/\\\",\\\"photos\\\":null,\\\"rating\\\":5,\\\"reviewCount\\\":3,\\\"pricing\\\":{\\\"pricingSource\\\":\\\"website\\\",\\\"isFree\\\":false,\\\"pricingType\\\":\\\"membership\\\"},\\\"placeTypes\\\":[\\\"point_of_interest\\\",\\\"establishment\\\"],\\\"lastUpdated\\\":null,\\\"dataQuality\\\":\\\"verified\\\",\\\"faqs\\\":[{\\\"question\\\":\\\"What should I bring for check-in at South Bay Dog Training Center?\\\",\\\"answer\\\":\\\"Bring proof of current rabies and core vaccinations, a leash for entry and exit, and an ID tag with up-to-date contact info to breeze through check-in at South Bay Dog Training Center. Download the waiver from http://www.southbaydogs.com/ and submit your dog profile before your visit.\\\",\\\"lastUpdated\\\":\\\"2025-11-14T19:36:02.813163+00:00\\\"},{\\\"question\\\":\\\"How does pricing work at South Bay Dog Training Center?\\\",\\\"answer\\\":\\\"South Bay Dog Training Center offers flexible memberships and punch cards so you can tailor visits to your routine. Contact the desk for the latest promotions or multi-dog discounts.\\\",\\\"lastUpdated\\\":\\\"2025-11-14T19:36:02.813163+00:00\\\"},{\\\"question\\\":\\\"Which amenities does South Bay Dog Training Center offer?\\\",\\\"answer\\\":\\\"The team rotates toys, agility props, and splash features weekly so repeat visits to South Bay Dog Training Center never feel stale. Expect shaded seating, rinse stations, and staff roaming the yards to keep playgroups safe.\\\",\\\"lastUpdated\\\":\\\"2025-11-14T19:36:02.813163+00:00\\\"},{\\\"question\\\":\\\"When is South Bay Dog Training Center open and where do I park?\\\",\\\"answer\\\":\\\"Hours rotate with weather and staffing, so call ahead to confirm current play blocks. Street and shared-lot parking is available nearby; arrive a few minutes early to grab a spot. Use posted signage around Gardena to navigate any temporary closures.\\\",\\\"lastUpdated\\\":\\\"2025-11-14T19:36:02.813163+00:00\\\"},{\\\"question\\\":\\\"How do I contact the team at South Bay Dog Training Center?\\\",\\\"answer\\\":\\\"For reservations, temperament assessments, or party rentals, call (562) 244-8126, and visit http://www.southbaydogs.com/. The concierge team at South Bay Dog Training Center typically replies within one business day.\\\",\\\"lastUpdated\\\":\\\"2025-11-14T19:36:02.813163+00:00\\\"}],\\\"email\\\":\\\"info@mysite.com\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"static\\\",\\\"listingType\\\":\\\"free\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"ChIJi3td0iDLwoARe0Q7YzWivWU\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"South Park Doggie - Adventureland (South Bay)\\\",\\\"businessType\\\":\\\"Dog Park\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"$34\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"south-park-doggie-adventureland-south-bay\\\",\\\"address\\\":\\\"945 W 190th St\\\",\\\"street\\\":\\\"945 W 190th St\\\",\\\"city\\\":\\\"Gardena\\\",\\\"state\\\":\\\"CA\\\",\\\"zipCode\\\":\\\"90248\\\",\\\"full_address\\\":\\\"945 W 190th St, Gardena, CA 90248\\\",\\\"latitude\\\":33.8587151,\\\"longitude\\\":-118.29236089999999,\\\"googlePlaceId\\\":\\\"ChIJi3td0iDLwoARe0Q7YzWivWU\\\",\\\"phone\\\":\\\"(310) 756-6110\\\",\\\"website\\\":\\\"https://www.southparkadventureland.com/\\\",\\\"photos\\\":null,\\\"rating\\\":4.8,\\\"reviewCount\\\":232,\\\"pricing\\\":{\\\"pricingSource\\\":\\\"website\\\",\\\"isFree\\\":false,\\\"pricingType\\\":\\\"membership\\\"},\\\"placeTypes\\\":[\\\"dog_park\\\",\\\"park\\\",\\\"point_of_interest\\\",\\\"establishment\\\"],\\\"lastUpdated\\\":null,\\\"dataQuality\\\":\\\"verified\\\",\\\"photo\\\":null,\\\"faqs\\\":[{\\\"question\\\":\\\"What should I bring for check-in at South Park Doggie - Adventureland (South Bay)?\\\",\\\"answer\\\":\\\"Bring proof of current rabies and core vaccinations, a leash for entry and exit, and an ID tag with up-to-date contact info to breeze through check-in at South Park Doggie - Adventureland (South Bay). Download the waiver from https://www.southparkadventureland.com/ and submit your dog profile before your visit.\\\",\\\"lastUpdated\\\":\\\"2025-11-14T19:36:02.813163+00:00\\\"},{\\\"question\\\":\\\"How does pricing work at South Park Doggie - Adventureland (South Bay)?\\\",\\\"answer\\\":\\\"South Park Doggie - Adventureland (South Bay) offers flexible memberships and punch cards so you can tailor visits to your routine. Contact the desk for the latest promotions or multi-dog discounts.\\\",\\\"lastUpdated\\\":\\\"2025-11-14T19:36:02.813163+00:00\\\"},{\\\"question\\\":\\\"Which amenities does South Park Doggie - Adventureland (South Bay) offer?\\\",\\\"answer\\\":\\\"The team rotates toys, agility props, and splash features weekly so repeat visits to South Park Doggie - Adventureland (South Bay) never feel stale. Expect shaded seating, rinse stations, and staff roaming the yards to keep playgroups safe.\\\",\\\"lastUpdated\\\":\\\"2025-11-14T19:36:02.813163+00:00\\\"},{\\\"question\\\":\\\"When is South Park Doggie - Adventureland (South Bay) open and where do I park?\\\",\\\"answer\\\":\\\"Hours rotate with weather and staffing, so call ahead to confirm current play blocks. Street and shared-lot parking is available nearby; arrive a few minutes early to grab a spot. Use posted signage around Gardena to navigate any temporary closures.\\\",\\\"lastUpdated\\\":\\\"2025-11-14T19:36:02.813163+00:00\\\"},{\\\"question\\\":\\\"How do I contact the team at South Park Doggie - Adventureland (South Bay)?\\\",\\\"answer\\\":\\\"For reservations, temperament assessments, or party rentals, call (310) 756-6110, and visit https://www.southparkadventureland.com/. The concierge team at South Park Doggie - Adventureland (South Bay) typically replies within one business day.\\\",\\\"lastUpdated\\\":\\\"2025-11-14T19:36:02.813163+00:00\\\"}],\\\"source\\\":\\\"static\\\",\\\"listingType\\\":\\\"free\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"62054c15-d8bd-44cc-9292-937f249938a9\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\